Furthermore tis to be known concerning Wine, That 
                              •
                           he Feces and Phlegm thereof is the Mineral as 'twere, and that the Substance of the Wine is the Body, in which the Essence is Conserved; even as the Essence of Gold lies in Gold. Therefore wee'l set down the Practise for a remembrance, that so we may not forget it: and 'tis thus;

Take the Quintessence of Bole, and of Iron, the Quintessence of Amber, (alias Cathebes) of each one pound;
